schema:name: Broadway: Hong Kong Cafe Photographs
schema:description:
1 - Geoffrey Chan loads up a plate as he prepares to serve a customer at Hong Kong Cafe.

2 - Persimmons given to the restaurant by a customer adorn the front area at Hong Kong Cafe.

3 - A cook ladles a selection into a takeout tray at Hong Kong Cafe.

4 - Chow mein noodles are prepared in the kitchen in preparation for the lunch crowd at Hong Kong Cafe.

5 - A chunk of pork is ready to be prepared for the day's offerings at Hong Kong Cafe.

6-8 - Hong Kong Cafe.

9 - A plate of fried wide rice noodles and beef at Hong Kong Cafe.

10 - Jack Newell of Davis, Calif., a regular at Hong Kong Cafe since his World War II days, has lunch.

11-12 - A customer has lunch while reading the daily newspaper at Hong Kong Cafe.

13 - The lunch crowd on a typical weekday at Hong Kong Cafe.

14 - The lunch crowd at a section of Hong Kong Cafe.

15 - Interior of a section of Hong Kong Cafe.

16 - Serving customers at Hong Kong Cafe.

17-19 - Exterior street view of Hong Kong Cafe.
